hyperlink to our victim here.", "tokens": [51364, 400, 550, 527, 1578, 11231, 510, 14790, 300, 12905, 300, 9848, 22473, 281, 527, 6760, 510, 13, 51614], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09270709014135944, "compression_ratio": 1.7651515151515151, "no_speech_prob": 0.021229753270745277}, {"id": 48, "seek": 15676, "start": 181.76, "end": 183.76, "text": " And through social engineering, something like that,", "tokens": [51614, 400, 807, 2093, 7043, 11, 746, 411, 300, 11, 51714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09270709014135944, "compression_ratio": 1.7651515151515151, "no_speech_prob": 0.021229753270745277}, {"id": 49, "seek": 18376, "start": 183.76, "end": 186.76, "text": " somehow tricks our victim into clicking on that link.", "tokens": [50364, 6063, 11733, 527, 6760, 666, 9697, 322, 300, 2113, 13, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06967572560386052, "compression_ratio": 1.8452380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 0.001971062971279025}, {"id": 50, "seek": 18376, "start": 186.76, "end": 190.76, "text": " And when that user clicks on the link and sends that request to the web server,", "tokens": [50514, 400, 562, 300, 4195, 18521, 322, 264, 2113, 293, 14790, 300, 5308, 281, 264, 3670, 7154, 11, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06967572560386052, "compression_ratio": 1.8452380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 0.001971062971279025}, {"id": 51, "seek": 18376, "start": 190.76, "end": 192.76, "text": " what's the web server do?", "tokens": [50714, 437, 311, 264, 3670, 7154, 360, 30, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06967572560386052, "compression_ratio": 1.8452380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 0.001971062971279025}, {"id": 52, "seek": 18376, "start": 192.76, "end": 194.76, "text": " Well, it does exactly what it's designed to do.", "tokens": [50814, 1042, 11, 309, 775, 2293, 437, 309, 311, 4761, 281, 360, 13, 50914], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06967572560386052, "compression_ratio": 1.8452380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 0.001971062971279025}, {"id": 53, "seek": 18376, "start": 194.76, "end": 199.76, "text": " It's receiving a valid request from a valid user, so it executes the requests.", "tokens": [50914, 467, 311, 10040, 257, 7363, 5308, 490, 257, 7363, 4195, 11, 370, 309, 4454, 1819, 264, 12475, 13, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06967572560386052, "compression_ratio": 1.8452380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 0.001971062971279025}, {"id": 54, "seek": 18376, "start": 199.76, "end": 204.76, "text": " And some funds are transferred to, say, the baddie's bank account.", "tokens": [51164, 400, 512, 8271, 366, 15809, 281, 11, 584, 11, 264, 1578, 11231, 311, 3765, 2696, 13, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06967572560386052, "compression_ratio": 1.8452380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 0.001971062971279025}, {"id": 55, "seek": 18376, "start": 204.76, "end": 207.76, "text": " So this is the heart of cross-state request forageory.", "tokens": [51414, 407, 341, 307, 264, 1917, 295, 3278, 12, 15406, 5308, 337, 609, 827, 13, 51564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06967572560386052, "compression_ratio": 1.8452380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 0.001971062971279025}, {"id": 56, "seek": 18376, "start": 207.76, "end": 210.76, "text": " It's that it's a valid request coming from a valid user.", "tokens": [51564, 467, 311, 300, 309, 311, 257, 7363, 5308, 1348, 490, 257, 7363, 4195, 13, 51714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06967572560386052, "compression_ratio": 1.8452380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 0.001971062971279025}, {"id": 57, "seek": 21076, "start": 211.76, "end": 213.76, "text": " And this is not actually as hard as you think it is.", "tokens": [50414, 400, 341, 307, 406, 767, 382, 1152, 382, 291, 519, 309, 307, 13, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 58, "seek": 21076, "start": 213.76, "end": 217.76, "text": " Because of one very interesting little technique that we have", "tokens": [50514, 1436, 295, 472, 588, 1880, 707, 6532, 300, 321, 362, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 59, "seek": 21076, "start": 217.76, "end": 219.76, "text": " that we use all the time on the web nowadays.", "tokens": [50714, 300, 321, 764, 439, 264, 565, 322, 264, 3670, 13434, 13, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 60, "seek": 21076, "start": 219.76, "end": 222.76, "text": " You've probably noticed when you log into a lot of websites,", "tokens": [50814, 509, 600, 1391, 5694, 562, 291, 3565, 666, 257, 688, 295, 12891, 11, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 61, "seek": 21076, "start": 222.76, "end": 224.76, "text": " you'll see that little button that tick-pock that says,", "tokens": [50964, 291, 603, 536, 300, 707, 2960, 300, 5204, 12, 79, 1560, 300, 1619, 11, 51064], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 62, "seek": 21076, "start": 224.76, "end": 226.76, "text": " keep me logged in for two weeks.", "tokens": [51064, 1066, 385, 27231, 294, 337, 732, 3259, 13, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 63, "seek": 21076, "start": 226.76, "end": 230.76, "text": " When you do that, what's being stored on your computer system is a cookie.", "tokens": [51164, 1133, 291, 360, 300, 11, 437, 311, 885, 12187, 322, 428, 3820, 1185, 307, 257, 14417, 13, 51364], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 64, "seek": 21076, "start": 230.76, "end": 233.76, "text": " So your system, every time you go to that website,", "tokens": [51364, 407, 428, 1185, 11, 633, 565, 291, 352, 281, 300, 3144, 11, 51514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 65, "seek": 21076, "start": 233.76, "end": 235.76, "text": " your system will send that cookie to the web server.", "tokens": [51514, 428, 1185, 486, 2845, 300, 14417, 281, 264, 3670, 7154, 13, 51614], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 66, "seek": 21076, "start": 235.76, "end": 238.76, "text": " And the web server will, that cookie contains a unique identifier.", "tokens": [51614, 400, 264, 3670, 7154, 486, 11, 300, 14417, 8306, 257, 3845, 45690, 13, 51764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06746155023574829, "compression_ratio": 1.8169934640522876, "no_speech_prob": 0.14134764671325684}, {"id": 67, "seek": 23876, "start": 239.76, "end": 241.76, "text": " And so the server knows, aha, that's you.", "tokens": [50414, 400, 370, 264, 7154, 3255, 11, 47340, 11, 300, 311, 291, 13, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 68, "seek": 23876, "start": 241.76, "end": 244.76, "text": " And so you don't actually necessarily have to have the user logged in", "tokens": [50514, 400, 370, 291, 500, 380, 767, 4725, 362, 281, 362, 264, 4195, 27231, 294, 50664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 69, "seek": 23876, "start": 244.76, "end": 248.76, "text": " right at that exact moment when the baddie here sends this request.", "tokens": [50664, 558, 412, 300, 1900, 1623, 562, 264, 1578, 11231, 510, 14790, 341, 5308, 13, 50864], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 70, "seek": 23876, "start": 248.76, "end": 251.76, "text": " It can often be hours, days later, after someone has logged in.", "tokens": [50864, 467, 393, 2049, 312, 2496, 11, 1708, 1780, 11, 934, 1580, 575, 27231, 294, 13, 51014], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 71, "seek": 23876, "start": 251.76, "end": 253.76, "text": " But because of these persistent connections,", "tokens": [51014, 583, 570, 295, 613, 24315, 9271, 11, 51114], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 72, "seek": 23876, "start": 253.76, "end": 255.76, "text": " these keep me logged in for two weeks.", "tokens": [51114, 613, 1066, 385, 27231, 294, 337, 732, 3259, 13, 51214], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 73, "seek": 23876, "start": 255.76, "end": 258.76, "text": " These types of attacks can often be performed much, much later.", "tokens": [51214, 1981, 3467, 295, 8122, 393, 2049, 312, 10332, 709, 11, 709, 1780, 13, 51364], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 74, "seek": 23876, "start": 258.76, "end": 262.76, "text": " Or the baddie here could first do a cross-site scripting attack", "tokens": [51364, 1610, 264, 1578, 11231, 510, 727, 700, 360, 257, 3278, 12, 30417, 5755, 278, 2690, 51564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 75, "seek": 23876, "start": 262.76, "end": 264.76, "text": " to obtain the user's cookie.", "tokens": [51564, 281, 12701, 264, 4195, 311, 14417, 13, 51664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 76, "seek": 23876, "start": 264.76, "end": 266.76, "text": " Lots of different ways of doing this.", "tokens": [51664, 15908, 295, 819, 2098, 295, 884, 341, 13, 51764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09908808680141673, "compression_ratio": 1.7114754098360656, "no_speech_prob": 0.014330320060253143}, {"id": 77, "seek": 26676, "start": 267.76, "end": 270.76, "text": " But here's the key thing that you need to know about cross-site request forgeries.", "tokens": [50414, 583, 510, 311, 264, 2141, 551, 300, 291, 643, 281, 458, 466, 3278, 12, 30417, 5308, 337, 32217, 13, 50564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 78, "seek": 26676, "start": 270.76, "end": 272.76, "text": " Who's the target of attack?", "tokens": [50564, 2102, 311, 264, 3779, 295, 2690, 30, 50664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 79, "seek": 26676, "start": 272.76, "end": 274.76, "text": " Ultimately, who is the baddie going after here?", "tokens": [50664, 23921, 11, 567, 307, 264, 1578, 11231, 516, 934, 510, 30, 50764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 80, "seek": 26676, "start": 274.76, "end": 277.76, "text": " Is it our user here or is it the web server?", "tokens": [50764, 1119, 309, 527, 4195, 510, 420, 307, 309, 264, 3670, 7154, 30, 50914], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 81, "seek": 26676, "start": 277.76, "end": 280.76, "text": " And ultimately, in cross-site request forgeries,", "tokens": [50914, 400, 6284, 11, 294, 3278, 12, 30417, 5308, 337, 32217, 11, 51064], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 82, "seek": 26676, "start": 280.76, "end": 283.76, "text": " the target of attack is the server.", "tokens": [51064, 264, 3779, 295, 2690, 307, 264, 7154, 13, 51214], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 83, "seek": 26676, "start": 283.76, "end": 285.76, "text": " So here's a quick summary.", "tokens": [51214, 407, 510, 311, 257, 1702, 12691, 13, 51314], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 84, "seek": 26676, "start": 285.76, "end": 287.76, "text": " In a module before we talked about cross-site scripting,", "tokens": [51314, 682, 257, 10088, 949, 321, 2825, 466, 3278, 12, 30417, 5755, 278, 11, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 85, "seek": 26676, "start": 287.76, "end": 290.76, "text": " here's a quick summary of the diff key differences between cross-site scripting", "tokens": [51414, 510, 311, 257, 1702, 12691, 295, 264, 7593, 2141, 7300, 1296, 3278, 12, 30417, 5755, 278, 51564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 86, "seek": 26676, "start": 290.76, "end": 293.76, "text": " and cross-site request forgeries.", "tokens": [51564, 293, 3278, 12, 30417, 5308, 337, 32217, 13, 51714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0904850959777832, "compression_ratio": 2.0082644628099175, "no_speech_prob": 0.0024773997720330954}, {"id": 87, "seek": 29376, "start": 293.76, "end": 296.76, "text": " So cross-site scripting, the major thing you need to remember here,", "tokens": [50364, 407, 3278, 12, 30417, 5755, 278, 11, 264, 2563, 551, 291, 643, 281, 1604, 510, 11, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06692558995793375, "compression_ratio": 1.8440860215053763, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005175999249331653}, {"id": 88, "seek": 29376, "start": 296.76, "end": 302.76, "text": " the target of attack in cross-site scripting is the user's browser, the client's browser.", "tokens": [50514, 264, 3779, 295, 2690, 294, 3278, 12, 30417, 5755, 278, 307, 264, 4195, 311, 11185, 11, 264, 6423, 311, 11185, 13, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06692558995793375, "compression_ratio": 1.8440860215053763, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005175999249331653}, {"id": 89, "seek": 29376, "start": 302.76, "end": 305.76, "text": " And in cross-site request forgeries,", "tokens": [50814, 400, 294, 3278, 12, 30417, 5308, 337, 32217, 11, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06692558995793375, "compression_ratio": 1.8440860215053763, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005175999249331653}, {"id": 90, "seek": 29376, "start": 305.76, "end": 308.76, "text": " the target of attack is not the user, but the server.", "tokens": [50964, 264, 3779, 295, 2690, 307, 406, 264, 4195, 11, 457, 264, 7154, 13, 51114], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06692558995793375, "compression_ratio": 1.8440860215053763, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005175999249331653}, {"id": 91, "seek": 29376, "start": 308.76, "end": 310.76, "text": " That's a very important difference to remember", "tokens": [51114, 663, 311, 257, 588, 1021, 2649, 281, 1604, 51214], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06692558995793375, "compression_ratio": 1.8440860215053763, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005175999249331653}, {"id": 92, "seek": 29376, "start": 310.76, "end": 313.76, "text": " between these two very common types of attacks.", "tokens": [51214, 1296, 613, 732, 588, 2689, 3467, 295, 8122, 13, 51364], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06692558995793375, "compression_ratio": 1.8440860215053763, "no_speech_prob": 0.0005175999249331653}], "language": "en"}